  <prompt>
    Refactor `src/solutions/DailyBriefing/src/hooks/useInlineTodoCreate.ts` to create `sprk_todo` records instead of writing `sprk_todoflag` on `sprk_event`. This was the final remaining functional `sprk_todoflag` writer outside the BFF (per task 013's schema-cut readiness audit). After this completes, the schema cut (tasks 004 + 005) can proceed without breaking DailyBriefing.

    Apply the same pattern established by tasks 020 (SmartTodo) + 013 (LegalWorkspace): consume the shared `CreateTodoWizard` from `@spaarke/ui-components`, OR if the inline-create flow needs to be programmatic (no wizard UI), build the sprk_todo record body directly + use `PolymorphicResolverService.applyResolverFields` for any regarding context.
  </prompt>

  <role>Spaarke Code Page developer with shared-lib consumer experience.</role>

  <goal>Zero `sprk_todoflag` + `sprk_eventtodo` references in `src/solutions/DailyBriefing/`. DailyBriefing's inline-todo-create flow creates sprk_todo records. Build clean. Schema cut tasks 004 + 005 unblocked.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>Task 013 (LegalWorkspace cleanup) discovered this last remaining functional consumer during its schema-cut readiness check on 2026-06-08. Audit Section 2D classified it but no task was assigned.</background>
    <relevant-files>
