  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `src/solutions/DailyBriefing/src/hooks/useInlineTodoCreate.ts` and any tightly-coupled callers. Understand the inline-create flow (is it programmatic, dialog-based, or otherwise?).</step>
    <step order="2">Grep `src/solutions/DailyBriefing/src/` for all `sprk_todoflag`, `sprk_eventtodo`, `sprk_event.sprk_todostatus` (or similar) references. Inventory the full scope.</step>
    <step order="3">Refactor the hook to create sprk_todo records: build the record body with sprk_name, sprk_notes, sprk_duedate, sprk_priorityscore, sprk_effortscore, ownerid, sprk_assignedto + any regarding context (use applyResolverFields for atomic resolver-field population).</step>
    <step order="4">Update any related types, services, and component callers in DailyBriefing.</step>
    <step order="5">If DailyBriefing has a SmartToDo or todo-display widget, repoint it to sprk_todo (similar to LegalWorkspace task 013).</step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm run build` in `src/solutions/DailyBriefing/` — clean.</step>
    <step order="7">Repo grep `src/solutions/DailyBriefing/src/` for `sprk_todoflag` + `sprk_eventtodo` — confirm 0 functional hits.</step>
    <step order="8">**Final schema-cut readiness check**: repo-wide grep for `sprk_todoflag` excluding `.claude/archive/` + this project's audit/spec/plan + JSDoc migration notes + frozen historical projects + compiled bundle artifacts → confirm 0 functional hits. This is the gate that unblocks tasks 004 + 005.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md status to ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">`src/solutions/DailyBriefing/src/hooks/useInlineTodoCreate.ts` (refactored)</output>
    <output type="code">Related callers / display components in DailyBriefing (if affected)</output>
